Pragmatic halos
Lasersohn proposes to understand imprecision in terms of a pragmatic halo (Lasersohn (1999)).




⟦five⟧ = {4:55, 4:56, …, 5:00, … 5:04, 5:05}
⟦X is dry⟧ = {True if 0 droplets, True if at most 1 droplet, …,                          True if at most 20 droplets}
⟦X is empty⟧ = {True if 0 seats filled, True if at most 1 seat                                 filled, …}
